    <item>
      <title>Participating in IABMAS 2024</title>
      <link>https://hamedmehranfar.github.io/talk/participating-in-iabmas-2024/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 09 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://hamedmehranfar.github.io/talk/participating-in-iabmas-2024/</guid>
      <description>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;OpenStreetMap with Leaflet&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&#34;utf-8&#34; /&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&#34;viewport&#34; content=&#34;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&#34;&gt;
    &lt;link rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; href=&#34;https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.4.0/dist/leaflet.css&#34; integrity=&#34;sha512-puBpdR0798OZvTTbP4A8Ix/l+A4dHDD0DGqYW6RQ+9jxkRFclaxxQb/SJAWZfWAkuyeQUytO7+7N4QKrDh+drA==&#34; crossorigin=&#34;&#34;/&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        #map {
            height: 400px;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div id=&#34;map&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;script src=&#34;https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.4.0/dist/leaflet.js&#34; integrity=&#34;sha512-QVftwZFqvtRNi0ZyCtsznlKSWOStnDORoefr1enyq5mVL4tmKB3S/EnC3rRJcxCPavG10IcrVGSmPh6Qw5lwrg==&#34; crossorigin=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
        var map = L.map(&#39;map&#39;).setView([55.66594919311265, 12.566368066937446], 16);
        L.tileLayer(&#39;https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png&#39;, {
            attribution: &#39;Map data © &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.openstreetmap.org/&#34;&gt;OpenStreetMap&lt;/a&gt; contributors&#39;,
            maxZoom: 18,
        }).addTo(map);
        var marker = L.marker([55.66594919311265, 12.566368066937446]).addTo(map);
        marker.setIcon(new L.Icon({
            iconUrl: &#39;https://cdn.rawgit.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-red.png&#39;,
            shadowUrl: &#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png&#39;,
            iconSize: [25, 41],
            iconAnchor: [12, 41],
            popupAnchor: [1, -34],
            shadowSize: [41, 41]
        }));
        marker.setIcon(new L.Icon({
            iconUrl: &#39;https://cdn.rawgit.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-violet.png&#39;,
            shadowUrl: &#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png&#39;,
            iconSize: [25, 41],
            iconAnchor: [12, 41],
            popupAnchor: [1, -34],
            shadowSize: [41, 41]
        }));
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;international-conference-bridge-maintenance-safety-and-management-iabmas&#34;&gt;International Conference Bridge Maintenance Safety and Management (IABMAS)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am excited to announce that I will be participating in the 12th International Conference on Bridge Maintenance, Safety and Management (IABMAS 2024) that will take place in Copenhagen, Denmark from June 24 to 28, 2024. My coalleagues and I host a &lt;a href=&#34;https://iabmas2024.dk/technical-programme/special-session&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;special session&lt;/a&gt; there. I also present a paper titled &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;Improving overviews of bridge interventions, possession windows, and costs&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo;. In this paper, we discuss how the integration of Building Information Modeling (BIM) and predictive maintenance models can be useful in bridge management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I look forward to presenting our work at the conference and receiving feedback from the experts in the field. I am also eager to reunite with familiar researchers and getting to know the new ones who share my passion for bridge engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I hope to see you in Copenhagen!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Workshop with Track management team @SBB!</title>
      <link>https://hamedmehranfar.github.io/post/2024-01-26-workshop-with-track-management-team-sbb/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://hamedmehranfar.github.io/post/2024-01-26-workshop-with-track-management-team-sbb/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Today, we had a productive workshop with the SBB track management team. We introduced our methodology to estimate intervention requirements, their costs, and required possession windows in the early phases of the intervention planning process. The workshop was well-received and we had a very good discussion afterwards. We exchanged feedback and ideas on how to improve and adapt this work to the specific needs and challenges of the SBB network. I am looking forward to working more closely with the SBB team to find the best ways to implement this work and support their decision making in the intervention planning process.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
